disp_name.description:
Name of the ability
Only necessary if the value differs from Harrier.

blurb.value: Valor periodically marks enemies as Vulnerable. Quinn's first basic attack against Vulnerable targets will deal bonus physical damage.

description.value: Innate: Valor marks enemies hit by Blinding Assault, Skystrike or targeted by Vault as Vulnerable, revealing them for 4 seconds. If no Vulnerable target exists for 1 second, Valor automatically marks a nearby visible enemy, but is not able to do so again for 8 − 2.93 (based on critical strike chance) seconds after the mark has timed out, was consumed or was overwritten by another mark.

description2.value: Quinn's next basic attack on-hit against a Vulnerable target consumes the mark to deal 10 − 95 (based on level) (+ 16% − 50% (based on level) AD) bonus physical damage.

description3.value: While Behind Enemy Lines is active, Harrier is disabled and all Vulnerable marks are removed.

targeting.description: Permafrost is a single target ability.

affects.description: Permafrost affects enemy champions and large monsters

onhiteffects.description: onhiteffects can be set to 'true', for abilities that apply on-hit effects (from items or other abilities)

occurrence.description: occurrence can either be set to 'hit' or 'attack', and refers to on-hit effects

spellshield.description: spellshield can either be set to true, or written with a custom description.

callforhelp.description: callforhelp determines whether minion aggro will transfer to the caster

additional.description: Displays additional information in a smaller window below the template.

notes.value:
* If a mark applied by an ability is overwritten, consumed, or timed out, Harrier goes on a 1-second cooldown if it's not already on cooldown.
 Harrier's targeting priority:
 Last unit hit (if it was a small minion it appears to select a different target).
 Lowest-health enemy champion.
 Lowest-health enemy minion.

 Harrier is consumed even if it is parried, the attack is negated in any case.
notes.description: Displays additional information with effect table to the right.

Name of the ability
Only necessary if the value differs from Blinding Assault.

width.value: 120

blurb.value: Quinn calls Valor to mark an enemy and hinder its vision before damaging all enemies in the immediate area.

description.value: Active: Quinn signals Valor to fly forward in a line in the target direction, stopping upon colliding with an enemy unit, dealing physical damage to them and all nearby enemies and applying nearsight to the target for 1.75 seconds, reducing their sight radius to 330 units.

description2.value: Non-champion targets are disarmed instead for the same duration.

description3.value: The nearsight persists through death.

Name of the ability
Only necessary if the value differs from Heightened Senses.

blurb.value: Passively grants Quinn Attack Speed and Movement Speed after she attacks a Vulnerable target. Activate to have Valor reveal a large area nearby.

description.value: Passive: Attacking a Vulnerable target grants Quinn  bonus attack speed and  bonus movement speed for 2 seconds.

description2.value: Active: Quinn orders Valor to reveal the area around her for 2 seconds.

description3.value: Enemies spotted are revealed for 2.75 seconds, reduced to 2 seconds for champions.

disp_name.description:
Name of the ability
Only necessary if the value differs from Vault.

target range.value: 600

blurb.value: Quinn dashes to an enemy, dealing physical damage and slowing the target's Movement Speed. Upon reaching the target, she leaps off the target, briefly interrupting it, and lands near her maximum Attack Range away from the target.

description.value: Active: Quinn dashes to the target enemy unit, knocking them back, dealing them physical damage, and slowing them by 50% which decays over 1.5 seconds, before leaping back and landing 525 units away from them.

notes.value: * Quinn will automatically attempt to attack the target once she completes Vault. The target will turn to face the opposite direction after being knocked back. Unlike its constant cast range Vault's bounce's can vary to allow Quinn to close or to make a gap between herself and the target (depending on casting position) or even to jump through a wall (if there is enough landing room on the other side). Quinn will track and follow the target if they move through dashes and blinks. This will not occur if the target is travelling to a very far distance (e.g, Recall, Teleport, Stand United). Vault also interrupts unstoppable basic attacks from affecting their target.*

disp_name.description:
Name of the ability
Only necessary if the value differs from Behind Enemy Lines.

blurb.value: Quinn and Valor team up to fly around at great speed.

description.value: Active: Quinn channels for 2 seconds. Upon completing it successfully, Valor picks her up and they unite, increasing her  total movement speed, granting her ghosting, and giving her the ability to use Skystrike. Behind Enemy Lines can be recast during the channel after 0.5 seconds.

description2.value: Taking damage from non-minions while Behind Enemy Lines is active causes Quinn to lose the  bonus movement speed for 3 seconds. Becoming immobilized ends Behind Enemy Lines immediately and puts it on  cooldown without performing Skystrike.

description3.value: Once Behind Enemy Lines has been learned, respawning or returning to the summoning platform will spawn Valor instantly, but Skystrike is disabled for 2.5 seconds upon uniting.

description4.value: Recast: Quinn cancels the channel, placing Behind Enemy Lines on cooldown.

notes.value: * Behind Enemy Lines does not refund its  mana cost if the channel was canceled via recast. The only exception is if Quinn's mana falls below the mana cost, in which case she is granted enough mana back (the equal amount needed) to be able to use Behind Enemy Lines again.
